(31, ' Hi and Welcome to Pakguns,\n\n\nPlease write a short introduction of yourself here.\n\n\nEnjoy your stay and Contribute your knowledge for everyone''s benefit.\n\n\nThanks,\n\n\nAbbas Malik', ''),
(32, ' Hi. My name is Shariq and i am an arms enthusiast with average knowledge about arms and ammo. I am really impressed with   Abbas''s knowledge and that is the reason i have joined this website.', ''),
(33, ' POF 9mm is   rs    40\n\nNorinco 9mm rs    38\n\nDarra    9mm rs    22\n\n\nSource: PAK ARMS KHI', ''),
(34, ' Salams Shariq and Congratulations ! You''re the first forum member of PakGuns. \n\nGood to have you here, tell your friends and colleagues about us. Let''s make this forum grow.', ''),
(35, ' Website Prices Section Updated.', ''),
(36, ' Hi guys\nthis is Waheed from lahore.i am very happy to see this site.we guys really need this over here.', ''),
(37, ' Salaams everyone! This is a great initiative Abbas sir and hope we get good representation from experts and users across Pakistan. I''m a Karachi-based practical newbie to guns so will be counting on everyone''s guidance in all things big or small. Happy & safe shooting! :cool:', ''),
(39, ' Hi guys. In your experience, what''s the best way to conceal carry a pistol if wearing trousers/jeans with no jacket? Average built person. What are the recommended good holsters available in Karachi?\n\nDo I need to carry the license also? Original or copy? BTW I''ve heard some mixed opinions but most people (including a CPLC guy) told me an all Pakistan license issued by Ministry of Interior Islamabad allows concealed carry, but not display. It mentions on pg 5 [i]"Licence for the possession of arms and ammunition [b][u]and for going armed[/u][/b] for the purposes of protection".[/i]', ''),
