(43, ' As advice I would not recommend that you carry your weapon on your person unless there is a real threat to your security. \n\nIt is subject to debate but it''s mostly illegal to carry a concealed weapon. The line you are quoting from the license (pg 5) is a general description of the usage of the license. If you look at page 29 of the same license first para, it says "he shall not take any such arms to a fair, religious procession or place of public assemblage". Any place where people are gathered (Parks, Markets, Offices, Restaurants etc even a bus) is classified as a place of public assemblage. Hence your taking the weapon there even with a license become illegal. \n\nBut all those are technicalities, the point is, Don''t carry your weapon on your person unless you *NEED* to.\n \n\nAs far the ways to conceal a weapon without wearing a jacket. There are three popular ways.\n\n1). Ankle Holster [img]http://www.uncle-mikes.com/images/ankle_holster.jpg[/img]\n\n2). Pocket Holster [img]http://www.uncle-mikes.com/images/inside_pocket_holster.jpg[/img]\n\n3). Belt Holster [img]http://www.uncle-mikes.com/images/side_bet.jpg[/img]\n\nAll of the above holsters are made by Uncle Mike''s which is in my opinion the best Holster making company in the world. They are available in the local market from Rs. 2000 - Rs. 5000.', ''),
