(59, 'Review: Viper Pump Action Shotgun (Turkish) Salams,\n\nI bought two .12 gague Vipers recently and tested them throughly. It is an excellent gun. Firing it reminds me of the Winchester Defender 1300. I think they tried to copy that design and did a fairly good job. Realibilty/durability seems good. As a mini test, I fired a box of 25 continuously only waiting for reloads. The barrel kept at a reasonable temperature and the entire box fired without a single jam.\n\nIt is a 5 + 1. The box includes an original pistol grip and the attached stock is simply beautiful. Highly recommended. I wish I bought more ! :)\n\nMy buying price was Rs. 25,000. Current price is around 30 K.', ''),
