(119, ' Hi Guys\n\nOk ill add my two bits here if no one minds. Ill just try to pass on the information I have from some source which include a Lawyer/A police office and a Gun enthusiast with connection, according to them "Concealed Guns should not be carried" regardless if you have a licence or not. Arms can only be kept in your personal property moveable or immovable. So if you are driving in your car you can keep a weapon for protection. But if you go to a public gathering please leave it in your car. That is what i do. \n\nHence i have imparted my two cents of knowledge. :)', ''),
(121, ' Abbas, \n\nI recently bought a turkish semi auto for about 50K. It called the volcanic. a friend of mine bought a tactical shotgun call the tomahawk for around 65k. And another friend mine purchased another semi auto shotgun called the Germernica for around 85k. From what i have seen in all they all seem to be coming from the same manufacture with new names stamped and slight modification.They are similar to your Viper in design only difference that that they are semiauto and not pumpaction.  The only problem that i see with the volcanic i have is that it does not come with a an alternate 26'''' barrell for hunting. So for the time being i am content with what i have till i either get an alternate barrell or change my gun. \n\nPS. Havnt test fired it yet, cant seem to get to a range, might use it on new years....:)', ''),
