(319, ' I''m a fan of the GSG 5. It''s a great little gun and the way it looks is worth the money, specially the one that comes with the silencer lookalike barrel cover. \n\n.22 generally don''t have any practical defense usage but as you said, they are some of the most fun weapons to use. Good on the range, good for Rabbits etc with a scope. A shotgun blows the little things to bits and the smaller pellets become a pain in the backside to get rid off once cleaning the animal. \n\nBullets are cheap as well. I wonder if the GSG can fire .22 magnums. If it can, those can be lethal.\n\nSomeone was telling me the other day that the security detail of the U.S President carry .22 handguns for accuracy. Any comments ?', ''),
