(376, ' And Taurus reliability depends on the model. The Taurus 24/7 IS unreliable and I would never think of carrying it as a defense pistol but the Taurus PT99 is another matter, I would use and prefer it over many other pistols for self defense. \n\nI have put every kind of ammo though the PT 99 and in 1000+ rounds I put though it, I have never had a single misfire regardless of what I feed it. I fed it ammo which the 24/7 wouldn''t fire even after 10 trigger pulls and the same round the PT99  fired instantly on the first go.\n\nIf Taurus would put the 24/7 grips on the PT99. It would become the most formidable low cost pistol in the world.', ''),
