(474, ' Regarding the quota license thing is that if you have made it with a dealer and if its a federal license then it should be ok because with provincial there are issues. The thing is that you get the form going unarmed and carry an original nic or driving license because they keep it at the enterance and tell the guy you want to go to the range. Im not sure about the office being open on Sat. Get the form becuase it takes time for the form to be filled in becuase of its requirements. It requires a police verification certificate to be signed by the SSP of your town and character ceritificate attested by two different gazetted officers not relatives. So the form takes time to be filled in. When you have completed the form you can go with the money and even armed when you submitt the form and money you can start shooting at that time but the thing is that it takes like a month for getting issued a permenent membership card becuase your application is submitted to the NI(naval intelligence) and then it is verified. First step they do is check whther you are a political activist or not and that is where you can have problems if you have a licnese issued on any political parties quotaa.', ''),
