(590, ' Salams,\n\nThere are some gun terms used in our posts that leave newer members scratching their heads, wondering what the heck [b]FTF[/b] or [b]HD[/b] etc mean ? Here''s a quick guide to Gun terms.\n\n\n\n[b]FTF[/b] = Failure to Feed\n\n[b]FTE[/b]=  Failure to Eject\n\n[b]HD[/b]  = Home Defense\n\n[b]SD[/b]  = Self Defense\n\n[b]NIB[/b] = New in Box, Unfired\n\n[b]PG[/b]  = Pistol Grip\n\n[b]SA[/b]  = Single Action (Where the hammer must be cocked manually prior to each shot)\n\n[b]DA[/b]  = Double Action (where pulling the trigger cocks the hammer and fires the gun)\n\n[b]Breech[/b] = The end of a barrel into which a cartridge is inserted.\n\n[b]Toe[/b] = The bottom of the butt-end of a gun stock\n\n[b]HP[/b] = Hollow Point (Bullets with a hollow tip, which allows the bullet to flatten out and expand upon hitting its target)\n\n[b]ACP[/b] = Automatic Colt Pistol\n\n[b]Butt[/b] = The end of a gun stock; the part that rests on the shoulder when the gun is mounted.\n\n[b]Choke[/b] = A carefully measured constriction of the bore of a shotgun at the muzzle, designed to control the spread of the shot as it leaves the barrel.\n \n[b]Muzzle[/b] = The end of a barrel, pointing towards the target, out of which the load is discharged.\n\n[b]FMJ[/b] = Full Metal Jacket. (A bullet that is completely enclosed in a jacket of metal, often copper. The jacket protects the softer lead core of the bullet, allowing deeper penetration of the target)', ''),
