(687, ' [quote=Abbas]Wsalams Conceal Carry and Welcome to PakGuns. I read in a post that you were gone for Hajj, MashAllah, that''s a great blessing. \n\nI couldn''t agree with your post more. Our aim is to create a responsible, educated close knit gun community in Pakistan.  \n\nInshAllah I won''t have to moderate anything judging from the quality of our members here. Everyone so far is mature and decent. Rest assured any illegal or abusive behavior will be acted upon swiftly. PakGuns is a good starting point for our club and we won''t let anyone ruin things for the rest of us. InshAllah I have no doubt we''ll graduate to a full fledge club with common benefits like cheaper ammo, firing ranges, shooting competitions, proper training facilities, licensing help and perhaps one day even our own gun dealership to give members discounted prices.\n\nTake care and good to have you with us.[/quote]\n\nThanks Abbas, I am sure your effort will bring lots of benefits to gun community in Pakistan.\n\nUnfortunately customer service is normally not a prime objective of gun dealers in Pakistan, We can use this forum to rate various dealers based on their pricing and service, thus helping other members to refrain from dealing with bad arm dealers, this would certainly help change their attitude and service standard and the dealers who charge exorbitant prices will be identified and will feel the pressure to be competetive.\n\nA sepeate section for this purpose can be set up where all dealers are listed (City wise) and standard rating criteria (quality of service, price, after sales service, quality of repairs, prices of ammo etc) can be defined which is to be filled by each member every time he deals with any dealer for whatever reason.\n\nI''m sure when such informatin is shared by the whole gun community of this country, there will be a termendous change in quality of service and related aspects.', ''),
(688, ' Is there any visible difference in the three guns, I think QSZ92 is the chinese millitary version capable of firing DAP rounds, CF98 is the same gun in civilian version. NP42 is only has a better barrel life than the CF98. These are my two cents about the gun, if anyone knows better please educate me.\n\nI onece seriously considered CF98 but didn''t bought it because of the trigger in the DA mode it was horrible, i have bigger than average hands but couldn''t pull the trigger all the way. In SA mode it was ok though. Whats your experience.', ''),
(689, ' Taurus pistols are regarded as junk by most in the US gun community, mostly because of their tendancy of the frame to crack around dissassembly pin. FTF & FTE are observed /reported after 200/250 rounds. No doubt they are good looking and shining but the workmanship and the quality of materilas used is poor. Only reliable pistols in their line are the bretta clones.\n\nDealers push them for two reasons, one large quantites were imported when there was a ban by most of the west on export of arms to Pakistan, two they are shiny and good looking and there is a myth in not so educated gun community that white (steel/alluminum) pistols are better, and hence yield better profits to dealers.', ''),
