(705, ' Thanks Abbas thanks acciprone and cap1 :), for ur assistance i will also look for this abbas bhai should i bhai pump action for self defence or automatic i have seen mossberg maverick, but i didnt knew the model i have a range of Rs.125 k so should i go for automatic / pumpaction and which 1 should i see i heard benelli,franchi are good,what about mossberg maverick 88?abbas bhai tell me are gas operated shotguns good enuff?? what abt winchester super x3,berreta extreme 2(alurika) are they the best shotguns in the world for self defence? actually i can purchase a high profile shotgun and at the moment i have 2 licenses free and i can to either purchase a best pistol for self defence (glock) and a good shotgun (franchi,winchester remington) or either best shotgun (winchester super x3,benelli, beretta xtreme 2) and a good pistol (stoeger)? what would u recommend?', ''),
(706, ' I think you should defiantly get the Glock :cool:\n\nAs far as the shotgun, if your primary usage is going to be sport then get a auto, it''s more fun, less recoil and faster firing, not to to mention slightly more accurate due to lack of elbow movement during pump action. \n\nIf you primary usage is for defense then I would recommend a short barrel (18 or 20 inch) pump action shotgun. They are cheaper, more durable & more reliable. I also like the sound of the pump, if your assailant hears it, it''s usually a good time for him to start running.\n\nWhich one should you get ? If you decide to go for the auto then all I''ve heard about the Berreta Extreme 2 is good things. \n\nFor pump action I have a bias towards Franchi because I''ve had one since I was 10. Over the past 20 years I''ve put a thousand + rounds though it and it has also been mistreated quite a bit by guards etc but it''s still going strong and fires like a champ. \n\nThe Maverick 88 is a reasonable gun provided you get the 18 inch or the 20 inch barrel one.', ''),
