(720, ' I carry with round chambered and thumb safety on near the hand brake of the car.  \n\n144 to my knowledge prohibits display of weapons and carrying of them on your person in a public area.  So if you have it in your car, 144 does not apply provided you do not handle your gun in sight of police.  \n\nAcciprone - The police can do something to you if you keep your gun on the dashboard unless of course you have a licence on which "DISPLAY" is ticked instead of just "PROTECTION".  Keep in mind that your arms licence is either display, protection or sports as mentioned on the first page.  If you have not been allowed display and you display your weapon, you are violating Pakistan Arms Act 1965 and can be arrested for it.', ''),
(721, ' [quote=bored2676]I carry with round chambered and thumb safety on near the hand brake of the car.  \n\n144 to my knowledge prohibits display of weapons and carrying of them on your person in a public area.  So if you have it in your car, 144 does not apply provided you do not handle your gun in sight of police.  \n\nAcciprone - The police can do something to you if you keep your gun on the dashboard unless of course you have a licence on which "DISPLAY" is ticked instead of just "PROTECTION".  Keep in mind that your arms licence is either display, protection or sports as mentioned on the first page.  If you have not been allowed display and you display your weapon, you are violating Pakistan Arms Act 1965 and can be arrested for it.[/quote]\n\n\nI guess i stand corrected. appreciate it .', ''),
