(896, ' Khan,u have to compare apples with apples not apples with oranges.NP-42/CF-98 is polymer frame and KanuniS is aluminum aloy frame.while NZ-85B is all forged steel constructed and Sarsilmaz B6 is polymer framed.\nSo,it can be like this CF-98 vs Sarsilmaz B6 and NZ-85B vs Kanuni S.\n\nNorinco pistols r very robustly made.they always use forged not cast steel for there pistols frame and slides.and there barrels r always chrome lined which is a big factor for long barrel life.\naccording to my knowledge,a aluminum frame pistol cannot out last a steel frame pistol.coz uneven metals wear quickly.and in aluminum frame pistol slide is always steel so it wears frame faster.\nin the case of CF-98,it has a modular firing control system.u can separate the whole modular part from the polymer frame which is actually act like a polymer grip only.that modular part takes all the firing stress.in Sarsilmaz B6 steel sliding rails r molded in the polymer frame when they make the frame.i hope i make this clear.', ''),
