(1045, ' If you guys have ever wondered what those little marks on the sides of our fire arms meant (CA, PSF, NDS etc).\n\nThey are symbols for:\n\nCA : Year of Manufacture (In this case CA = 2006, so CB = 2007 etc.)\n\nPSF : Smokeless Powder Firearm or (Polvere Senza Fumo)\n\nNDS: German state of Niedersachsen (Place of Manufacture)\n\n\nHere are two guides for the more popular proof marks.\n\n\n[url]www.pakguns.com/art/proofmarks.pdf[/url]\n\n[url]www.pakguns.com/art/proofmarks2.pdf[/url]\n\n\nI have stored it at our own site to ensure continued and fast access.', ''),
