(1561, ' @acciprone, if you like pump actions, then better look for Winchester Ranger, it comes with a 18" tube and a 28" with Winchoke Sysytem. it can serve the dual role of hunting, real or clay birds of your choice and home defense.\none thing which i think a must on any shotgun is a stock. [b]pistol grip only [/b]shot guns look good only in movies. in real life situations,you cannot hit anything without a proper stock. the best shotgun is which is available & fits you best. with out going into details of drop at heel & comb or length of pull, select a shotgun which fits you better, and in your budget.\nDBBL shotguns are usually thought as outdated especially for self defense. Arms dealer are the largest advocate of this idea. a few days ago i saw a gentleman on a gun shop who sold a very beautiful Robust shotgun & got a local PGO pump action in exchange. the DBBL are still suitable for self defense role, if one knows its way around the gun. a double trigger DBBL has two complete machinisim at work. two complete hammers, two firing pin two trigger two main springs& two tubes. actually you can say that two complete guns are joined together. so if one set goes wrong, you have one one full gun in working order. just my .02 paisas\ncheers', ''),
