(2080, ' Welcome Ka-Khan.\nGenerally, I suggest this subject may be referred as ''game'' rather than hunting. Term ''hunting'' is inclined towards poachers'' approach & game is otherwise,  as  termed internationally. To use guns for small or big game & wings is a debatable issue, same like shooting the poor little circle (at the range) all the life with different guns & thousands of bullets. Or its like having a Hummer at home to drop kids to school. Game is not all about killing animals, its a recreational package with bits of everything like hiking, trekking, survival, off-road driving, gun knowledge, shooting skills, outdoor living, navigation skills, local culture & landscape knowledge, etc etc. \nPeople who are into wild game, enjoy all this in one go and thats the fun part of it. Ask any of them & one will know that on an average they hardly shoot one box of cartridges / shooter during the whole trip and that does''nt mean its one shot one kill always. Use of ammo is even less when it comes to rifles.\n\nMost of the game lovers do know & ensure that it should not be a breeding season & secondly try not to hit a female if possible. And trust me they do care about this.\n\nShooting few birds or animals during the permitted season will not eliminate them a Allah Tabark Wataala created the reproduction of halal species in such a way that they are meant for our food. They will not finish. Check the list of extinct or to-be extinct species & the common denominator will be ''haraam'' species regardless of the geographical inhabitance.\n\nAs far a the number of these species going alarmingly low is concerned, its because of illegal gaming i.e. during breeding season & in game reserves & poaching. One example to support the comments above is quails, although it the same case with other species also, as almost everyone has this knowledge. When enthusiasts go for quail shooting, they will be able to get on an average 10 or 15 in a day''s trip. On the other hand a person who catches them with the net strip will be able to score anything between 50 to 75 from one field. These wild quails fetch a higher price that the farmed quails and there is no cost of breeding them. Isn''t it a lucrative business at a small scale. Talking of which, its because of lack of earning resources that trigger such risky means of bread & butter. But collectively, it comes down to policies (which are there always) & the honesty of the responsible officials.', ''),
