(2089, ' I think try GAMO as they make really good airgun and they are available at a reasonable although higher than Dubai prices. They are almost half the price of Diana. The good thing about airgun is that u can carry around town for wings shooting & no one will ask u a question. In the neighborhood, no one will complain & its excellent for target practice at almost negligible cost. I give credit to my brother airgun that I used when we were kids for my whatever little skills in target shooting.\n\nThe only thing I''ll suggest is that do get a branded gun as its the precision airgun is meant for, otherwise a TT can damage a person as much a GLOCK if placed accurately.\n\nGAMO should be around the price u mentioned.\n\nAs for the airport issue, I think airguns do not require permits or anything but still, as I was overloaded, I paid Dhs 5/kg for the 2 guns I brought to a ''khaypia'' in Sharjah & delivered to my address in Lahore. Thats it.\n\nAs u will see on the relevant info of the gun I have, its much more powerful than Diana 35 that is sometimes available in Pakistan. This one has a recoil reduction mechanism which makes it more expensive other airguns without this system. It has a fixed barrel, and the whole thing is much heavier than normal guns (a minus point). Its long effective range & its weight requires a telescope & simultaneously a bi pod to enjoy its true spirit.', ''),
