(2361, ' Firstly I won’t leave it on the dashboard where the sun hits it directly and I think it’s not even legal. The best places for it are passenger side dashboard compartment, under floor mat, under the seat. I keep mine in centre box behind gear and hand break with my license and extra magazine. I don’t really think there is anything wrong with a loaded gun if the car locking system is ok and has alarm system as well. You don’t want someone to steal your gun and commit a crime with it. If you are going to leave the gun at home then what is the use of having it in the first place for self defense.', ''),
(2362, ' well I never mentioned leaving it on dashboard in plain sight. When I carry in car, it goes under a box right below the steering, clearly not in sight but readily accessible by either hand. My concern was that if I had to park my car under direct sunlight, what would be the chances of a bang. Many a places u cant take your gun with u e.g. banks, other places etc & have no choice but to leave it in the car. \nAnother usual case is like some one carries the gun but his place of work doesn;t allow weapon & he can''t take it there even concealed but want/need to carry it with him when coming from/to office. Now he has no choice but to leave it in the car whether in trunk, under the seat etc. Now the car will most probably be parked in direct sunlight for a good 6 hours or even more. Now the chances? That is basically my point.', ''),